  "prompt": "Is it normal to have a dark ring around the iris of my eye?",
  "response": "A dark ring around the iris of the eye, known as a \"limbal ring,\" can be normal and is common in many people. This ring is often more pronounced in younger individuals and can fade with age. \n\nIn some cases, a dark ring can indicate certain health conditions, such as high cholesterol or other lipid disorders, if it appears suddenly or is accompanied by other symptoms. If you're concerned about any changes in your eyes or vision, or if the dark ring is accompanied by other symptoms (like pain, changes in vision, or irritation), it's a good idea to consult with an eye care professional for a thorough evaluation.",
